author: CNN
description: Lane Kiffin announced Sunday he will leave Ole Miss to coach at Louisiana State University (LSU), a Southeastern Conference (SEC)-foe. CNN’s Carolyn Manno reports on the “difficult decision” Kiffin says he made.
title: Lane Kiffin leaves ole miss for $100M LSU contract

author: CNN
description: Arizona Democratic Sen. Mark Kelly says he is not intimidated by President Trump suggesting that Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth should open an investigation into Kelly for urging service members to disobey illegal orders.
title: Sen. Kelly says Trump, Hegseth are 'threatening' him for telling the truth

author: CNN
description: The White House confirmed President Donald Trump will discuss Venezuela in a meeting with his national security team today as his administration intensifies its pressure campaign on the country. #CNN #News
title: Trump holds meeting with national security team on Venezuela

author: CNN
description: First responders rescued a skier after a chairlift malfunctioned in Wisconsin due to a power outage. 14 people who were stuck on the chairlift were successfully evacuated, according to CNN affiliate WISN.
title: Skier rescued off chairlift after power outage

author: CNN
description:
More than 70 million people are under winter alerts as a rapidly intensifying storm brings heavy snow, dangerous travel, and over 6 inches of accumulation for parts of the interior Northeast and New England.
#cnn #news
title: Bomb Cyclone to bring Northeast snow

author: CNN
description: The White House released a memo from President Donald Trump’s doctor saying that his MRI in October were for his cardiovascular and abdominal systems and that both showed “perfectly normal” results. #cnn #news #politics
title: White House releases statement about Trump’s MRI result

author: CNN
description:
Homeland Security Secretary Kristi Noem says the suspect in the Washington, DC National Guard shooting was "radicalized" in the US after arriving from Afghanistan in 2021.

Boris Sanchez and Briana Keilar speak with CNN senior law enforcement analyst and former FBI deputy director Andrew McCabe. #CNN #News
title: Noem: National Guard shooting suspect 'radicalized' in the US

author: CNN
description: Luigi Mangione, the 27-year-old accused of killing a health insurance company executive in a brazen attack that sparked a national debate, is appearing in court Monday as his attorneys seek to have his diary entries and other key evidence tossed from his state murder case.  #CNN #News
title: Luigi Mangione appears in court as his attorneys seek to have key evidence tossed

author: CNN
description:
Pope Leo XIV addressed a large crowd of young people in Bkerke, Lebanon, just outside of Beirut, on Monday. Leo encouraged them to stay in their home country to help foster peace across the Middle East. CNN's Christopher Lamb reports.

#CNN #News #Pope #Lebanon
title: Pope Leo meets with 15,000 young people

author: CNN
description: A federal appeals court ruled Alina Habba, President Donald Trump’s former personal attorney, is serving unlawfully as US attorney for New Jersey.
title: Appeals court rules Alina Habba is unlawfully serving as US attorney

author: CNN
description: CNN's Betsy Klein gets an early look at First Lady Melania Trump's White House Christmas decorations. #CNN #News
title: White House unveils Christmas decorations

author: CNN
description:
Donald Trump won the 2024 election in the Seventh District of Tennessee by 22 points, making it a "ruby-red" strongly Republican district. Democratic state Rep. Aftyn Behn is running in the special election tomorrow to replace GOP Rep. Mark Green, who resigned to take a private-sector job.

CNN chief data analyst Harry Enten examines the landscape of special elections, in which Democrats this year have been outrunning Kamala Harris's 2024 performance. Manu Raju also looks at the Tennessee race with his "Inside Politics" panel: USA Today's Susan Page, the Atlanta Journal-Constitution's Tia Mitchell and CNN senior reporter Stephen Collinson.  #CNN #News
title: 'Even a close GOP win tomorrow would be a bad sign for them': Enten on TN special election

author: CNN
description: Winter hasn’t even officially started, yet the vibe is already approaching full late-February fatigue. A new storm is barreling out of the Plains toward the Northeast, threatening more travel disruptions after a post-Thanksgiving blast dropped record November snow in Chicago, shut down highways across several states and triggered thousands of flight cancellations. CNN's Derek Van Dam and Pete Muntean report, and Sara Sidner speaks with Clint Henderson, managing editor of The Points Guy, about the outlook for holiday travel. #CNN #News
title: New winter storm brings fresh holiday travel headaches

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump expressed optimism after a high-level meeting between US officials and a Ukrainian delegation in Florida on Sunday. With Special Envoy Steve Witkoff en route to Russia, CNN's Chief Global Affairs Correspondent Matthew Chance breaks down what barriers are left to the talks.
title: Analysis: American diplomacy faces the test of the Kremlin

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump will hold a meeting at the White House on Monday evening about next steps on Venezuela, sources familiar with the matter told CNN, as the administration intensifies its pressure campaign on the country. Former NATO Supreme Allied Commander James Stavridis weighs in on rising tensions between the US and Venezuela.  #CNN #News
title: Former NATO commander makes prediction about possible land action in Venezuela

author: CNN
description:
US President Donald Trump expressed optimism after a high-level meeting between US officials and a Ukrainian delegation in Florida on Sunday, suggesting there was a “good chance” of a deal to end Russia’s war in Ukraine. US special envoy Steve Witkoff is traveling to Moscow on Monday, where he is expected to meet with Russian President Vladimir Putin, a US official told CNN.

CNN chief international security correspondent Nick Paton Walsh reports from Kyiv, and John Berman speaks with Rep. Adam Smith (D-WA), ranking member of the House Armed Services Committee. Audie Cornish also discusses the talks with her "Group Chat" panel: USA Today's Francesca Chambers, The AP's Michelle Price and CNN senior media analyst Sara Fischer. #CNN #News
title: Trump: Ukraine talks going well; 'good chance we can make a deal'

author: CNN
description: Stars of Paddington's London's West End musical took to the blue carpet as the show opened on Sunday night. The production is based on the series of children's books by Michael Bond and follows Paddington as he moves from Peru to London. #cnn #paddington #london
title: Paddington the musical opens on London's West End

author: CNN
description: Russian missile barrages and power cuts. This is the daily reality of war for civilians across Ukraine as diplomatic negotiations continue, with President Trump's Special Envoy Steve Witkoff heading to Moscow. CNN Chief International Security Correspondent Nick Paton Walsh reports from Kyiv. #CNN #news
title: Stakes high for peace talks as Kyiv faces power cuts

author: CNN
description: Lawmakers from both sides of the aisle voiced serious concerns over the weekend over reports on a follow-up strike that killed survivors on an alleged drug vessel in the Caribbean, with some suggesting it could constitute a “war crime.” Rep. Mike Turner, an Ohio Republican who serves on the House Armed Services Committee, said the follow-up strike was “completely outside of anything that has been discussed with Congress” about the Trump administration’s strikes on alleged drug vessels in the Caribbean.  #CNN #News
title: GOP lawmakers question legality of second strike on alleged drug boat

author: CNN
description: A shooting at a family gathering in Stockton, California killed four people and wounded at least 11 others, according to the San Joaquin County Sheriff’s Office. #cnn #news #shooting #stockton
title: Birthday party mass shooting leaves 4 dead

author: CNN
description: Heavy rainfall has unleashed widespread flooding and landslides across Indonesia, Thailand, and Sri Lanka. CNN's Ben Hunte reports. #cnn #news #floods #indonesia #thailand #srilanka
title: Deadly storms ravage Asia

author: CNN
description: Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro made his first public appearance in days on Sunday. He has not been seen since Wednesday, ending speculation he had fled the country. CNN's Stefano Pozzebon reports from Caracas, Venezuela. #cnn #news #venezuela #shorts
title: Maduro makes first public appearance in days after rumors he fled

author: CNN
description: Fareed gives his take on the modern US presidency: Walter Isaacson, author of “The Greatest Sentence Ever Written”, joins to discuss the Declaration of Independence and ask what is the American dream.   #CNN #News
title: Fareed's Take: The modern presidents wield authority far beyond anything the founders envisioned

author: CNN
description: President Donald Trump expressed trust in Secretary of Defense Pete Hegseth who says he did not order a second strike on an alleged drug vessel, following a Washington Post report that the secretary issued an order to “kill everybody” on a September strike. #politics #trump #cnn
title: Trump says Hegseth 'did not say that' following 'kill everybody' report

author: CNN
description: Trump expressed optimism following Sunday’s US–Ukraine meeting in Miami, telling reporters the talks are “going along well” and could yield a deal to end Russia’s war. CNN's Jessica Dean is joined by Political and National Security Analyst, David Sanger, and Democratic Rep of Massachusetts, Jake Auchincloss.      #CNN #News
title: US and Ukraine navigate 'delicate' peace talks
